<article id="post-110" class="post-110 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-creative-commons category-free-libre-culture category-piracy category-publishing tag-artistic-ownership tag-business-models tag-carbon-footprint tag-creative-commons tag-digitization tag-ecology tag-entertainment tag-free-culture tag-freedom tag-intellectual-property tag-kindle tag-libre-culture tag-new-media tag-open-culture tag-public-domain tag-scarcity">
	<header class="entry-header">
		<h1 class="entry-title">eBook Piracy</h1>
	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	<div class="entry-content">

		
		<p>During an interview on the Colber Report, Sherman Alexie made the statement: &#8220;With the open-source culture on the Internet, the idea of ownership &#8212; of artistic ownership &#8212; goes away.&#8221; Then prompted by Colbert, added: &#8220;It terrifies me.&#8221;</p>
<table style="font-family: arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 11px; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; color: #333333; background-color: #f5f5f5; height: 353px;" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="360">
<tbody>
<tr style="background-color: #e5e5e5;" valign="middle">
<td style="padding: 2px 1px 0px 5px;"><a style="color: #333; text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;" href="http://www.colbertnation.com" target="_blank">The Colbert Report</a></td>
